<p><i><b>Body and Soul</b></i> (1931) is an action and drama film directed by <a href="/wiki/Alfred_Santell" title="Alfred Santell">Alfred Santell</a>. The story, adapted from the stage play <i>Squadrons</i> by <a href="/wiki/Elliott_White_Springs" title="Elliott White Springs">Elliott White Springs</a> and A.E. Thomas, depicts <a href="/wiki/Royal_Air_Force" title="Royal Air Force">Royal Air Force</a> pilots in <a href="/wiki/World_War_I" title="World War I">World War I</a>. The film stars <a href="/wiki/Charles_Farrell" title="Charles Farrell">Charles Farrell</a>, <a href="/wiki/Elissa_Landi" title="Elissa Landi">Elissa Landi</a>, <a href="/wiki/Humphrey_Bogart" title="Humphrey Bogart">Humphrey Bogart</a> and <a href="/wiki/Myrna_Loy" title="Myrna Loy">Myrna Loy</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-3"><span>[</span>N 1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p></p>
